What you don't see: The wind knocked me down about 12 times (major bruised my butt), I got soaked from gales of rain, there were many tourists staring at me in confusion, and my dress was covered in sheep sh*t.... I am completely in love with Scotland. 😍

Shot on Sony a7R III with 24-70mm f/2.8
#alphacollective #alphafemale @sonyalpha

I finally took a fresh self-portrait this morning and had it all edited and ready to post here (even went swimming for the shot), and then I looked at the outtakes... And, well, this one's better. So here's Pepper, looking more magical than I'll ever be. 😂💕

Forever imagining the beauty of what these woods once were. 💙

Shot on Sony a7R III with 24-70mm f/2.8
#alphacollective #alphafemale #BeAlpha @sonyalpha

I tend to go into some sort of deep zone each time I'm shooting self portraits. The usual things that hold me back suddenly don't exist. I'm fully present, yet fully gone from the regular world. Everything else falls away. I feel the cold, but not unbearingly as I usually do when standing by - I'm one with it. Often 2-3 hours (or more) will go by before I realize I've been in this zone for that long and my body remembers it probably needs coffee.
Maybe nature casts magical spells on me.
Maybe I'm just a dork. 😜

But I'm grateful for the peace this process brings me. 😊

Shot on Sony a7R III with 24-70mm f/2.8
#alphacollective #alphafemale #BeAlpha @sonyalpha

That awkward moment when you have grand expectations to stand on a giant rock for a photo, but then realize you can't even climb it 6 inches off the ground... so you casually strike a "lost in wonder" pose and stand beside it like that's what you meant to do along along. 💁🏼‍♀️ Re-sharing this photo from last year because that sunset was too good not to re-live. 😍

Today on my stories I shared a few people whose work has immensely inspired me lately. I hope to make it a weekly thing to share some of my favourite artists on this platform. And not just to share, but to find new inspiring people also - which begs me to ask you guys: Who are some Instagrammers that inspire you lately? I'd love to expand my horizons on this app! Tag them below! 😊 ❤️

September 1st. The nights are getting colder again, the midday sun shines from an angle, the tips of leaves are beginning to turn golden, and the fog has been creeping through the early mornings again this week. My favorite season is right around the corner... I'm ready for it. 😊

Just spent the last several days off the grid chasing "autumn" in the Canadian Rockies... Highlights include:

More winter than autumn, almost 60 km trekked, 2400 meters elevation gained, one lost tent at the end of a 13 hour, 22km day of slow snow slogging (plus another extra 5 km for me running back up the mountain pass in the middle of the night to find it, to no avail 😂), 2 extra cozy nights with three of us crammed in my one remaining tent, 1 massive loaf of focaccia bread that may have saved our lives, 4 days total being bad-ass mountain babes and coming out alive on the other side.

To sum it all up, basically a much-needed trip that seamlessly combines pain with pure, jaw-dropping beauty... Reminding me all over again why I do the things I do. And also why I so appreciate sitting in a cafe with a warm cup of coffee. Balance. 😊 ✌️

Currently on my way home after a few days in Vermont and NYC. The city experience is a whole different world to me, and exciting as it is, I almost feel like I can't get home fast enough to my foggier, rainier, and all around naturey-er (is that a word?) elements. Feeling more and more grateful to be able to live in a place I truly love, and equally grateful to have opportunities to experience other places that deepen my perception of the world and appreciation for everything I once took for granted. 💕

What about you fine folks, do you consider yourself more of a city slicker or a nature hermit? 😎

The mornings have been deliciously foggy lately, I've been spending every spare moment here in my happy place, soaking in the magic. 😍

Fun fact: I had to desaturate the greens in this. A lot. This forest is so fluorescent it almost hurts. 🙈💚
